    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7358" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεῖραρ</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ατος</span>: (1) pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πείρατα</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ends, limits;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γαίης καὶ πόντοιο,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 8.478</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            τέχνης</span>, ‘tools,’ ‘implements,’ which bring to completion,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 3.433</span></i>; ‘chief points’ in each
          matter, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.350</span></i>; sing.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">decision</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          18.501</span></i>, cf. <i><span class="en">Od. 23.248</span></i>.—(2)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">cord, rope;</span> fig., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὀλέθρου
            πείρατα</span>, ‘snares’ or ‘cords’ of destruction, cf. Psalm
          xviii. 6, 2 Sam. xxii. 6; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὀιζύος</span>,
          ‘net’ of woe, <i><span class="en">Od. 5.289</span></i>; so <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πολέμοιο, νί̄κης</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 13.358</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
